<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dothnyell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just hit 14th level and was just wondering how you guys have your spells arranged in your books. Thanks...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pzar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well<P>I use the first pages to hold the spells usually in my spell lineup. Then comes the ones I need to be able to access fast.<BR>Last and least I put all obsolete spells in the back.<P>Pzar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just put them in my spell book as they came in level rank.<P><BR>Sure it means flipping the pages a bit here and there, but the /book command really helps a lot.  Most of the time I can get within a page or 2 of where I want to be.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>59th Dwarven Templar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aandain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have set up a hotkey bank to be able to get to the pages I need quickly. Some of the pages have blank spots, but you don't have to worry about flipping back 20 pages when you only have to hit one hotkey.<P>Main (/book 1) All my heals that I currently typically use (Greater/ Superior/ Complete/ Group), Valor, Guard, Root, Stuns.<P>2nd (/book 3) Backup spells, not used as often as the first set. Symbol (will have 2 symbols here when I get the peridot version), atone, bind, gate, stuff like that.<P>Resist (/book 5) One side has all my resists, the other side has all my cures.<P>DD (/book 7) Not just DD, but I know what I mean. Has one side with my undead DD and fears, other side with my regular DD, AoE DD (even if I never use it), and regular and AoE fears<P>Summon (/book 9) I haven't bought food since I was a newbie, and I don't want to start now. Summon food, water, hammer.<P>Misc (/book 11) Stuff that doesn't fit anywhere else, extinguish fatigue is the one I end up using most from here. Other various buffs or whatever, like the imbue gem spell, that haven't been made obsolete by higher level spells, but I rarely use.<P>Way in the back about /book 20 is where I start piling all the earlier versions of the spell lines. Rarely ever go back here, except when I feel like practicing conjuration and want to cast single foods or waters while waiting on a boat or something.<P>I usually end up doing some shuffling every new set of spells, but that's part of the fun of getting them.<P>Oh, and my #10 hotkey is /sit off, which is what it is on my primary hotkey bank as well, (with all my characters, usually), so I don't have to think about it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Georgia_TKR</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I organized mine by spell types: Healing, Buffing, Symbols, Resists, Cures, DDs, Rezzes, Undead DDs, Utilities, and obsolete spells.<P> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Georgia Gaelicmyst<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Everlore Staff Member<BR>http://www.everlore.com/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Trilvan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My first page is my normal spell load out for hunting in a group. <BR>Page 3 is some of my backup spells and some spells that I will load in and cast upon logging in. Summons of food water....<BR>Page 5 is all of my dd and fear spells. Also includes roots, enstill, basicly this is my combat spells. <P>Past page 7 I have all of my earlier versions arranged so that they have 2 or 3 pages for each line and they are all together. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Page 1:<BR>Remedy<BR>Complete Heal<BR>Word of Healing<BR>Divine Aura<BR>Divine Barrier<P>Page 2:<BR>Root<BR>Immobilize<BR>Ressurection<BR>Abolish Poison <BR>Couteract Disease<P>Page 3:<BR>Heroism<BR>Heroic Bond<BR>Armor of Protection<BR>Shield of Words<BR>Symbol of Naltron<P>Page 4:<BR>Resist Magic<BR>Resist Poison<BR>Resist Disease<BR>Resist Fire<BR>Resist Cold<P>Page 5:<BR>Upheaval<BR>Banish Undead<BR>Retribution<BR>Gate<BR>Bind Affinity<P>Page 6:<BR>Atone<BR>Stun<BR>Holy Might<BR>Force<BR>Sound of Force<P>Page 7-10:<BR>everything that I still sometimes use that I don't use often enough to put before<P>Page 20-50:<BR>Obsolete versions of spells or stupid spells I never use (Like True North)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gniss Fleshmender</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">page 1-2   Heals<BR>Page 3-4   Cures/utility<BR>page 5-6   Buffs<BR>Page 7-8   Resists<BR>Page 9-10  Damage/stun/root<BR>page 11-12 summons/misc<BR>page 13-50 Outdated/ultrararecast spells<P><BR>I've used this setup for so long that I can open the book to the right pages for a certain spell without thinking.<P>------------------<BR>The patchwork cleric<BR>Domus Divinae<BR>Prexus</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aanar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">at 56:<P>page 1: obsolete dd<BR>level 5 dd is still useful for ensuring faction "hits", or as a fast casting pull spell after lulling<BR>page 2: obsolete ae dd<BR>page 3: obsolete summoned dd<BR>page 4: summon food/water/pet/hammer invigorate<BR>page 5: 5 stuns<BR>page 6&7: remedy, DL, CH, celetestial, word of vigor, rez, cure disease/blindness/posion<BR>page 8&9: dd, undead dd, ae dd, imobolize, fear, undead fear, gate, anul<BR>(have this as the page that comes up with spellbook hotkey)<BR>page 10: rm, rp, rf, rc, rd<BR>page 11: group hero, shield, marzin, pinzarn, fortitude<P>The rest is sorted by type and rarely used.  This way I only have one spell book hot key in my main bank and can flip one page to the left or right to get just about any spell I'd need to load in normal fighting.  Heals are just about always loaded anyway, though memming cure posion and such does come up.  Any spell I'd need on short notice or am swapping in and out alot is on the main page (ie gate, fear).  I move stuns in and out a lot, but they pretty much have to be loaded ahead of time anyway.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Scrubbles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Okay, here is the cool method:<P>Make a /Book 7 key<P>On pages 7 and 8 put stuff you swap a lot.  buffs, gate and such.  This becomes the central page of your book<P>Page 5 and 6 you put common offensive spells.  DD, Roots, Stuns, Fears.  Use page 3 and 4 for spillover and rarely used stuff ie. earthquake, pacify, etc.<P>Page 9 and 10 are for current other spells that are memmed often.  Heals, Resists, Divine Line, Rez, etc.  11, 12 and 13 are spillover.<P>Non Used spells get buried at pages 25+.<P>The reason for this configuration is that every spell I use can be accessed by switching one to two pages.  No more flipping through 10 pages to find that resist poison.  Make sure to have gate on page 7 as when you have divine aura or barrier up, it will be a quick mem to get gate fired up.  Flipping pages when close to death is not something I like to do.<P>Phinnin <BR>45 Cleric<BR>Scrubbles<BR>52 Druid-Retired<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">BinaaVZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have the spells in my first line up on page 1 then have the most common alternates on second and some other usueful spells on third and forth ..rest is in the back.<P>I used to have all my spells in the order i got them. Cause i was so used to have it like that before you could move spells.<P><BR>Binaa<BR>Defiant<BR>57 Cleric<BR>Vallon Zek<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I do:<P>page 1/2 heals<BR>page 3/4 buffs<BR>page 5/6 offensive spells<BR>page 7/8 offense/utility<BR>page 9 buffs for noobs<BR>page 10-12 other non-obsolete spells<P>pages 30-50 obsolete spells arranged by spell line<P>I really have only 2 pages to flip tops 90% of the time, and the other 10% it's 3 pages, makes for fast spell selection.<P>Heals: Remedy, Celestial Healing, Complete Heal, Word of Restoration, Divine Light, Extinguish Fatigue, Ressurection, Heroic Bond, Antidote, Counteract Disease<P>Buffs: Heroism, Armor of Protection, Symbol of Marzin, Bulwark of Faith, Holy armor  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">, 5x resist buffs<P>Offensive spells: Stun, Holy Might, Stun Command, Sound of Force, Atone, Reckoning, Exile Undead, Root, Force, Annul Magic<P>Offense/Utility: Upheaval, Cancel Magic, Nullify Magic, Immobilize, Gate, Bind Affinity<P>I forget after that as the rest are junk and not important, crap like summon food and fear spells and pacify</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AeolwindStormrunner</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Page 1:  CH, Remedy, Divine Light, Celestial Healing, Celestial Elixir<BR>Page 2:  Bond, Mark, Aegis, AoP, MoK<BR>Page 3:  Group heals<BR>Page 4:  DA, DB, Aegolism<BR>Page 5-50:  Absolutely no clue.  I have hotkeys that bounce me around my book.  They are sorted by type so I have a ROOTS, STUNS, DAMAGE, AE, POISON, BUFFS, RESIST, ZING, and a few o