 rearranging, I found the easiest way is to put basically any spell I would use in the first 6 or so pages of the book.  After that, I organize each spell by importance.  IE, first all the heal spells, then all the buff spells, then I think all the evo spells, etc.<P>In the first few pages, I have all the heals I would use, my resses, atone + all the stuns, buffs, DA/DB, fear, roots, dispel, gate, bind, etc.  Basically any spell that you would use with some sort of frequency.  I think this is the best way to organize in my opinion.  Very accessible.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">bellsong</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My hotkey to mem spells is " book" which is /book 5<P>Page 5 is gate, root, fear, atone etc...<P>go to the left ( pages 1-2 and 3-4) are buffs and heals ( in that order)<P>go to the right ..<P>7-8 is damage, stuns<BR>9-10 is other combat ( lull, other fears etc)<BR>11-12 is undead <BR>13-14 is misch crap like summons<BR>15-16 are " somesones dead" spells..rezz's and divine etc<P><BR>pages 40-50 are all the old ones</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thistleburr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Greetings!<P>Page 1 (Heals)<BR>Complete Heal, Divine Light, Remedy, Celestial Elixir, Word of Restoration<P>Page 2 (Hey I died)<BR>Divine Aura, Divine Barrier, Reviviscence, Gate, Bind Affinity<P>Page 3 (Undead)<BR>Sunskin, Improved Invis to Undead, Panic the Dead, Banish Undead, Exile Undead<P>Page 4 (Stuns)<BR>Stun, Holy Might, Force, Sounds of Force, Stun Command<P>Page 5 (Buffs)<BR>Heroic Bond, Naltron's Mark, Bulwark of Faith, Armor of Protection, Symbol of Marzin<P>Page 6 (Resists)<BR>Resist Magic, Fire, Cold, Disease, Poison<P>Page 7 (Travel and combat spells)<BR>Immobilize, Invoke Fear, Retribution, Mark of Karn, The Unspoken Word<P>...<P>Page 24 (seldom used buffs)<BR>Aegolism, Divine Intervention, Yau